,Recommended,271240,27373847,"Posted: 24 November, 2016",all,Das Blah,"I first went into the game adoring the feel and wishing for it to be a longer classical tycoon style game.I'm so glad it isn't.This game is an incredibly intelligent and unique strategy game that requires players to manage a company and successfully out-play their competitors in short to intermediate matches, where the objective is to buy out the oppoisition. With limited claims, a♥♥♥♥♥♥of resource types and locations players will have to adapt their strategy to what they can get their hands on, and if a competitor is getting a bit too powerful, players can use a series of corporate espionage actions in order to temporarily cripple parts of their competitors, to get that slight edge.Everything about this gamem requires you to think ahead and plan out what you want to do, while being able to adapt said plan to the ever evolving playing field that competitors provide. Your stocks might suddenly be bought or maybe someone decided to shut down your production, and it's through this that you have to carefully adapt and react to these situations. The interactions between players is done incredibly, with fast-paced gameplay that'll keep you on the edge of your seat the whole time.Accompanying this is of course beautiful and stylized graphics combined with incredible sounds and music to create the perfect mood, depending on where you're at in the game. They successfully managed to make Mars up close beautiful, and after the release of recent DLC, they did the same with Ceres.While the lack of players is definitely a problem, the AI is honestly one of the best I've seen in any game. The devs have spent so much time and money on making an extremely intelligent AI that can adapt and plot just as well as the player, and will create many intense moments where you and the competing AI are racing to buy the other's last stock, with the most satisfying feeling when you finally manage to beat them.Ultimately this game is incredible and definitely deserves a try, though it may not be for most casual strategy players. You'll find hours of entertainment, whether it's through the AI or other players that by some magical chance you manage to find. GG Mohawk, GG."
