76561198037752430,Recommended,271240,22745179,"Posted: 1 May, 2016",all,SolutOdka,"Offworld Trading Company is a new genre of game, which is a blend of several styles into its own new style. A fine balance bringing to the table an awesome game.On some sides, it reminds me of the old RTS Monopoly Tycoon, with the multiplayer capitalism management on one hand and the real time business sim on the other hand. (The auction system is by the way fantastic !) While at the same time, the game is grand by its simplicity of the resources manegement and strategy planning, maybe similar to Settlers with the logistics supply chain of raw materials up to the final produces.This game can enter into the History of Gaming, that it is at the same time a smart game, with in depth game anaylyzis without having dozens of parameters, just a few interesting resources with different rules and needs which intricately are depending on each other in a beautiful supply and demand concept.And at the same time, it is a game fun to play, where you don't have to learn dozens of recipes, where you quickly have fun (a few tutorials teach you the basic ropes of the game, same as chess, the game can be learnt in a very short time, but it can require a long time to master :)!). Lots of events occur in game, which can change the whole course of a development, pirates intercepting your cargos, mutiny of your geothermal powerplant at the very wrong time... well you get the picture hehe !You might be thinking that this game sounds like a very long game to play, spending hours of planification, development and implementation ... such as a Heart of Iron, Total War or a Civ game for instance ... well not at all, the games lasts hardly more than 30 minutes ! And this is in the case you are not losing after a few minutes!All in all, this game, is, I believe, refreshing with its new genre, smart with its simple but challenging puzzles mechanics for the colonization of Mars, all this while having a good fun when utilizing the resources of the planet.The question is ... will you challenge yourself ... go play this legendary Offworld Trading company ?"
,Recommended,271240,29866193,Posted: 11 February,all,Dat Necron Boi!!!,"TL;DR - I like the game for attempting a different and solid approach to the stategy genre and I recommend it for the slower-paced buy highly chaotic nature of matches themselves, but it certainly isn't everybody's cup of tea so if you're not into those things, or expect the traditional RTS experience, give this game a pass.There's certainly a divide among the people who've tried this game, I think it stems from a clashing between a misunderstanding of the game's main concept, the expectations from watching a couple of gameplay videos and playing the game itself, which is understandable because this isn't a game that's easily put in a few words.It seems that people are now associating RTS with APM and fast reflexes exclusively, which is another reason why this game is such a departure for most of the users who try it. Out of the gate, this game is nothing like the traditional RTS: you aren't microing units, you aren't building an army, you aren't going for the high APM, you aren't scouting bases or out-blobbing the opponent's blob army. Instead you are making decisions for the most part, decisions that impact the course of the game over time instead of immediately, leading to a slower paced game based around matches of wits and constantly monitoring a wide variety of indicators that are further influenced by the chaos theory that stems from the many other choices that other players are making during a match.This is a game that demands close observation of numbers and the things that affect those numbers so that you make informed decisions that lead to you out-witting the competition over matches that are certainly longer when compared to other multiplayer games, especially those that belong to more recent launches. It's also a game that assumes that you can properly learn its rules, which is why the training wheels come off sooner and there's huge rifts in the handholding in between difficulty settings. The computer doesn't cheat the higher you go (at least, if you don't go higher than manager which is the standard difficulty), it just reacts sooner and expects you to keep up the pace through, again, decisions based on proper vigilance of information and indicators.I admit to having a bias for this kind of game, since I really like strategy games, especially those driven by economic aspects and this one is certainly all about the incredibly unpredictable nature of economics and a caricaturization of the cutthroat corporate environment which all serves to keep me engaged and entertained, making for a good game in my book considering both the beautiful audiovisual design and the solid mechanics. At the same time, I find it easy to empathize with the people who get put off by this game, its rules are certainly different, it demands different things from the player, and matches themselves never tend to play out the same way twice, even on the exact same conditions because there's always something else that you, and the remaining players, can choose to do.I thoroughly recommend the game but only if you like slower paced games with lots of stuff happening at the same time, along with learning new things and experiencing a different kind of strategy games. If you aren't one for patience, expecting the standard fast-paced, high APM, insane reflexes gameplay, I suggest you go for something else."
76561198034423970,Recommended,271240,25102693,"Posted: 23 August, 2016",all,UberPooky,"OTC is an excellent game that is a lot deeper than first appears. There are some surprisingly varied strategies available. Playing different scenarios is a good way to experince some of the variety this game has to offer. I like that it plays quickly and you can complete a whole game in a reasonable length of time. It is a pretty unique experience in that it is real time, but it is not about military conflict, but rather economic conflict. There is also an impressive level of polish to this game from the graphic design to the well thought through interface. I'd highly recommend this to someone who is interested in strategy games."
