,Recommended,271240,20582035,"Posted: 17 January, 2016",all,Donnie Totoro,"Offworld Trading Company , although still in early access, does a great job of defining stages to the flow of a match. Why do I mention this first? Because the best RTSs I've played have loosely defined stages that allow for depth of strategy at each step. Available funds  are precious early in a match and there are several outlets to utilize these funds. You can upgrade early to try and get a lead in resource gathering, you can use the black market to shut down your opponent's income, or you can manipulate the market to make it more costly for other players to catch up to you. As the game progresses, the options available to you also expand, and strategies abound.The mid-game in Offworld Trading Company is where the most important blows start being traded. In order to ensure your company is not bought, you must purchase and hold onto at least 5 of your own stock (which then have to be bought out all at the same time in order for another player to remove you from the game); however, the money available to you to buy your own stock could also be used to take out another player by beating them to 6 of their stock. This makes decisions on who to buy stock in, whether to purchase your own stock, or whether to continue to upgrade to get a lead in the late game potentially deadly. If the wrong choice is made, other players will take advantage of your mistakes.Late game, if the game hasn't already been decided by the mid-game brawl, comes down to endurance. Each remaining player's goal is to get enough money to buy out the others before being bought themselves. There are several advanced buildings in Offworld Trading Company that allow for varying strategies to accomplish this task and, depending on the state of the market, each strategy has a place and can allow for you to outspend your opponents.An economic RTS is a fairly unexplored idea, so be prepared to endure a fairly high learning curve before becoming competent in the gameplay. I'm sure most of what I've mentioned in the paragraphs above means very little to someone who hasn't played Offworld Trading Company , but the point is to show the depth of gameplay Offworld Trading Company allows for.So, let's break this game into its parts:Content: 5/10Multiplayer is where this game shines. There is a campaign mode, but it is currently very limited.Animations: 9/10There is little animation in the game, but what has been done is done well.Graphics/Artwork/Illustrations: 9/10Once again, there are few graphical elements required for this style of game, but the graphics are this gen. and well done.Gameplay: 10/10Loads of depth to multiplayer games, and a good pacing built in to the gameplay.Controls:10/10I would only give less than a 10 in this category if there was no ability to change hotkeys or the controls were unresponsive/glitchy. Although I do not like the layout of the default hotkeys, I don't consider that a reason to downgrade this category.Reliability: 8/10The game is still early access and some bugs are being worked out. There are some issues with making lobbies and changing hosts mid-game that are being worked out, as well as a few smaller glitches.User Interface (UI): 9/10Very well put together to give an overview of how the game is progressing as well as easy access to your options. I took away a point because I think that the notification system could use some work when you are targeted by the black market or a shortage/surplus occurs.Music and Sounds: 10/10Some sounds are still being created, but the recently added new music and the completed sounds are very well done.Originality: 10/10I can only imagine how difficult it must be to enter a new sub-genre into the books. Soren Johnson and his team have done a great job in developing this original idea.Community Vibe: 10/10The developers listen closely to player feedback and are very active on the forums. The game is updated on a regular basis and has improved with each iteration.Total Score: 90/100If you're a fan of RTSs or enjoy market manipulation, I can highly recommend this game to you. If you enjoy a challenge, Offworld Trading Company will provide it to you. This is aGame You Absolutely Must Have:) .Although there is plenty of room for casual players in this game, with its current player base of dedicated fans, I'd recommend people who put themselves in this category to watch some videos of the game before deciding to purchase.Here is a video of some higher level gameplay with good commentary:https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=V0GaPMCA86o"
