, economy, variability, and overall complexity,  Kind of sad that its almost over before it begins...I am recommending this game because of its uniqueness and potential but on a scale of 1-10 this game is a 4, at least for the price."
76561197974422069,Not Recommended,271240,22883989,"Posted: 9 May, 2016",all,Jungle George,"I put this game on my wishlist based on the Pedigree of the developers. It seemed an interesting and different take on an RTS and it looked like a harsh business trading simulator. I bought it on sale at 35% off and that came with a free key for a buddy. Called my go to buddy to give it to him and he said ""Oh man, I already have it and you are not going to like it. It's fun for a couple of hours but that's it. It's too simplistic to enjoy much longer"".Sadly, he was dead on. The game is extremely simplistic. So if you are looking for the varied and intersting types of games you could get from Civ, you won't find it here.I literally enjoyed it for about 4 hours and that was pretty much it. You have four factions who are largely identical. They all make a variation of mines and factories which make exactly the same core components. You take those core components and build one or more of 5 different buildings that can give you an edge like help you produce resource X a bit faster, or get a monopoly on a tech like teleportation, which eleminates the need to transport your goods to your home base.You can then begin to sell your goods to try and make money to buy out your competitor faster than they can buy you out.In the meantime there are a handful of repetitive, boring, dirty tricks you can use to slow them down or speed you up in your pursuit of the one goal, which is buy your competitors out.That's it. That's the whole game. Their variety pitch is that there is an infinite number of ways to play each match because you won't always use the same dirty tricks, but there are only a handful of dirty tricks.If you are interested in a repetitive experience of skirmish matches which last 15 - 60 minutes, and you like fine tuning your ability to deliver the same strategy over and over, then this game is for you.If you are looking for a deep, strategic, intereting RTS with a variety of playstyle and paths to victory, then absolutely not.As polished as the game is, one can see that there is very little depth or substance. My go to gaming friend nailed it when he called it ""simplistic"". Wish I had called him before I bought the game. I'm going to have to bust it out once a month or so to get in some skirmishes and still have it feel fresh and get my money's worth out of it."
