76561198086137165,Recommended,271240,23709272,"Posted: 22 June, 2016",all,AlienAsparagus,"One of the most complex resource management games I've ever played.What I found charming about the game is how it simulated not just the basics of economics but it had elements of consumers, terrain (including weather effects), sourcing and patents. Players are also able to manipulate some of these factors through the 'black market' basically debuffs or buffs you can buy on a periodic basis.Not counting for daily challenge or multiplayer, there are essentially 2 game modes.Skirmishes are 1 off rounds where all buildings are available and your goal is to buy off the shares of your competitors to win.If you like progression then campaign mode is pretty nice. Instead of buying your oponents, you buy buildings for the settlers on the colony to win which would also help you tamper with supply and demand (Personally I built more houses so I could drive the price of food and oxygen up lulz). it adds a little more depth to the game as you do not own every building and would have to choose which buildings you'd like to acquire or upgrade though the downside is that this mode lasts for only 7 rounds.TL:DRFairly complex with a variety of strategies to win and ♥♥♥♥ over your oponent that doesn't make you rage quit.Realistic resource manager cause it adheres to a lot of basic business and economics principles."
