,Recommended,271240,28496638,"Posted: 20 December, 2016",all,StrykerNoStriking,"I've had this game since it was in beta, and was the first game I ever streamed on Twitch. Even when its graphics, characters, and music were sketchy as hell, the core gameplay was enticing enough for me to spend HOURS learning how to read the stock market, fake out other players, and understand how I lost.This isn't Civ. This isn't a turn-based strategy or another RPG (both of which are my more usual fare). It's a game that's like... like chess with the stock market on Mars. There are a limited number of moves/buildings/resources and only one way to win--but infinite strategies to get there.If you like chess-on-steroids while you're competing against the clock, you'll love this. If you're looking for a narrative or something closer to Civ, go elsewhere--but keep this in your library when you're ready to stretch your brain a bit."
