,Recommended,271240,16816256,"Posted: 30 June, 2015",all,motstandet,"A deceptively fast-paced economic, base-building strategy game with no military units.Offworld plays very well in a FFA environment, and I enjoy 6- and 8-player games regularly. It keeps you on your toes as players react to changing prices, trying to make profits. You need to be constantly asking yourself, ""what resources are the other players neglecting?""It can become quite frenzied in the end game as you buy up a couple other players and suddenly you need to manage ~60 structures, trying to gain cash faster than your rivals, who are trying to buy out your company.Trash those Glass Furnaces, drop down Reactors, research Oxygen production because it's selling for 60k offworld. Your rival has more Offworld Markets; better sabotage his shipments or oxygen production...Every game is different with randomized maps and resource distributions. Black Market (aggressive abilities and other utilities) is also switched up. There isn't really a build order; need to look at the map and the other colonies to figure out the best overall plan, which will definitely change several times during the 20 min game.It's fun."
