76561198006543535,Recommended,271240,16532968,"Posted: 19 June, 2015",all,El Guapo,"4x strategy without combat and Stephen Hawking doing the voice-over!Graphics serve their purpose, the interface is sharp and controls in general feel very polished. This looks and feels like Civilization 5. Just do yourself one favour: turn off both the music and the sound effects.It's a business game that offers a lot of macro economic goodness. Supply and demand at its core, resource shortage, bottlenecks, dirty tactics.This game offers the best a.i. I've ever seen and it's still far from finished. The a.i. doesn't cheat on low to medium difficulty settings and it still gives me a tough fight for my money.I'll give you an example what the a.i. did to me:I was totally reliant on my next two steel shipments. The a.i. evaluated my situation, hired pirates and intercepted those vital steel shipments. I went bankrupt because I was used to games offering poor a.i.. I was aware of the bottleneck in my supply chain. Hell, I'm even writing a paper on supply chain management RIGHT NOW! And the a.i. was set on the 3rd of 8 difficulty levels! This should have been a walk in the park.Well, I learned from it. After 3 hours of playing I'm pistol-whipping this little ******. I own the a.i. (on level 3 of 8). Now it's time to be a man and face it at 50% of its might. :DThe price:I got it on 50% summer sale. For 19 quid it offers fantastic value. I would go as high as 30. Wouldn't pay 40 though just yet. It's too steep for an early access game. Wait for a decent sale and get it if you enjoy economic games.The con:There's only one problem with the game and unfortunately it's a major one: the performance is sub par. The game is rather cpu-heavy. I got a decent system (i5-4660, gtx 960, 8 gb ram) which is way above min reqs. The cpu seems to be the bottleneck and it shouldn't be really. It's just a matter of poor programming (no multi-core support maybe?).-----------------------------------------Update: As of beta 4 the performance has improved significantly and is actually pretty good now.Update: The game is in beta 5 by now. Many improvements again. Farther zoom level, balance, more campaign features etc.Having played it for 45 hours now in total, I can easily recommend it. Still not burned out on it in any way.rating: 9/10"
