76561198074191940,Recommended,271240,22765265,"Posted: 2 May, 2016",all,Rahdukes,"Plenty of other reviewers have shared their two cents. I'll keep my review on the leaner side.If you enjoy fluid, real time, dynamic strategy games you should consider Offworld Trading Company. There are no invading forces, no armies, no tanks. It's a about cunning and guile. Trying to read the market, trying to manage your company while discerning your opponents strategy. Skirmish games can be over relatively quickly (under an hour) and usually leave you wanting more. This is a nice change of pace from a game like Civilization where even on the shorter end of the spectrum games will last 2-3 hours. That said, I do love the Civilization series, which is part of the reason why I purchased this game.In terms of learning curve - the game is easy to pick up, difficult to master. I say give it a go."
