76561198089533667,Recommended,271240,14441909,"Posted: 12 February, 2015",all,Hotchinaboy,"I played the tutorials and I felt that this game is a masterpiece.You played as a trade company on Mars, the system is quite simple and you would feel relax first time play it. But other compines, which is one of a great settings in this game, could ""kill"" you slowly like cancer - by buying your stock. You can purchase other players or AI's stock, they can also purchase yours. Who own the stock, who own the company. Better company, higher stock price. If your stock price is very high; it will be nearly impossible for others to ""slay"" you. To increase the stock price by trading and annex other companies.The market system is pretty simple. Players sell iron, the iron price falls, Players buy steel, steel price goes up. Supply and demand. You mine the materials and build factories to process them into higher price product.There are also some speical buildings in the game. Cash maker make stable income, Lab enhance technology, hacker control the market price etc.The black market is an amazing setting. It allows players to do illegal activities to damage, interfere or even bribe others' industry. I played aganist AI and I used EMP stopped his manufacturing. He got no money and I started to purchase his stock. Then I annexed him and I won the game.-ProsGreat graphic, not realistic, but beautifulMarvelous music and soundBalanced system and challengesTerrific theme, a landmark of RTSFour totally different factionsDifferent ways to win a gameComfortable Control-ConsCannot play offline-AdviceAdd Workshop and Map Editor pleaseMore planets in sequel, interstellar trade will be cool"
