,Recommended,271240,16529258,"Posted: 19 June, 2015",all,MisterMentat,"In this game you are the CEO of a company that is trying to establish a foothold on Mars. You balance managing resources and growing your company with nuking your opponents mines, tampering with their water supply, and buying shares in their company with the ultimate goal of acquiring all of your competitors businesses. You buy and sell resources on the open market, and the price of goods is reflected by the supply from you and your competitors, their demand, the distribution of resources on the map, and the demands of the Martian colony.It's a very tense ""economic RTS"" from the designer of Civ IV. This is an RTS more about timings, resource management, and awareness than micromanagement. If you love the city building, economic portion of strategy games like Civilization, but you also like the cut-throat, edge of your seat action of games like Starcraft or Warcraft (but weren't always the best at managing hudndreds of units) then this game is amazing.There is a very distinct feel to every game, and I don't think I've ever played another game quite like this. I think it's a blast, and I can't wait to see where this game goes in the future."
