76561197967950117,Recommended,271240,18573483,"Posted: 19 October, 2015",all,HawsJon,"This is another one of those games where they took the basic RTS idea and tried to change it enough to make it fresh and interesting. Shockingly, they pulled it off.This is an economic RTS, which means no direct combat. You win by buying all the stocks of your opponents. Don't think this means no conflict. The games sabotage system is rather brutal and you will have ample opportunity to harass your opponents as well as get bent over by the AI.This brings us to the computer controlled players. They will completely kick your♥♥♥♥♥on higher difficulties. According to the developers, the AI does not cheat, they are just that good. Although this might sound like a bad point it is in fact a positive. You can lower your handicap enough that you can learn to play without getting insta-killed to learn and then ramp up the difficulty later.There are a wide variety of resources to collect and even more production items you can make with those resources. Many of them are required to progress and anything you do not make yourself must be purchased. Although there is a limitless supply of resources to purchase, the more an item is bought the higher the price becomes. Likewise the more you sell resources the cheaper they become. It is a constant balancing act that becomes quite enjoyable.Multiplayer is fantastic. You can easily partner with a buddy and share resources. This means you can each focus on specific raw resources and manufacturing. When you build two of the same types of buildings next to each other, they gain an adjacency bonus of 50%. With three touching the adjacency bonus is 75%. This means that building two of the same building next to each other does not double production, it triples it. This is a huge advantage in co-op play.At this time the game is listed as early access. I would disagree and say it is release quality. We have played probably 50 games with no glitches ot crashes of any kind. The game is solid, balanced, challenging and fun. Completely worth a buy."
