,Recommended,271240,19363754,"Posted: 29 November, 2015",all,omony,"This is a very nice RTS. The only RTS I'm playing now (so I finally abandon AoE and Rise of Nation). So i think the idea worth the price (I've bought it on sale, though). The realisation as well is expensive (good AI, stable code). So I was surprised to see just ""mostly positive"" as a summary of user reviews. I really want this game to be fully published.Point by point:1. No blood. You do not have to rise and command an army. Still, you are able to be offensive and there are plenty of things you do have to command.2. True fast-paced RTS - you can limit your gaming time to one round - to 30-50 minutes. You do not have to do low-level micromanagment, you have to be fast as well as smart. However, there are meditating moments as well.3. Very original. I had to spend an hour just to learn what are the rules. And these are very interesting rules. There are simularities with Civilization (and Catan as well). Still, this is something new for me. Basically, you have to buy opponents' companies. There are different strategic decisions you have to do - which type of base to build, whether to invest or not into intellectual property (patents), wich materials you have to mine, which you are able to buy in the market, which type of energy to choose, do you want to use lending or not. There is a lot of tactics here as well. So.. The rules are balanced and there is a lot to master here. However, they still tune the balance so you might find one day that the game had changed and you have to adopt.4. The rules are tunebale. So you can turn off some of the things people are complaining about in other comments and make the game more balanced and make the ""rush"" stratagy more hard to implement.5. The AI is strong. So offline is challenging as well. Looks like there is online option - never tried that.6. Nice GUI, music and animations. No crashes - high level of coding for early access.So if you enjoy economic part in RTS games or if you enjoy both RTS and Civilization-like games, you defenitely should try this one. This is a new kind of experience."
