76561198006029791,Recommended,271240,22911003,"Posted: 11 May, 2016",all,Greymalkin,"Short version, I liked this game.Longer version;At 5 hours of play I loved this game.At 10 hours of play I thought this game rocked all out.At 15 hours of play I was wanting more.At 20 hours of play I probably wont play this game very much anymore.Offworld Trading Company is an excellently balanced economic/base building/strategy game.  But in some ways it is too well balanced in that while there are 4 different styles of play based on the base you choose, those 4 different styles of play have very little opportunity for variation within themselves.Even on the mid-range difficulty levels I found that you had to play a particular way determined by your base type and too much variation was usually a quick way to lose.On the upper difficulty levels forget about trying something new, either you play a flawless game with a very specific and particular build order (and hope you don't get disproportionally screwed over by the black market) or you might as well not have bothered starting the level.Now none of the above makes it a bad game, but unless you are the sort who has a hard-on for the multiplayer experience or grinding out every ""Do X 100 times"" achievements OTC has limited replayability.   I enjoyed my 20 hours of play and have no regrets on the purchase but probably will never reach 25 hours of play."
