76561198025172964,Recommended,271240,14634604,"Posted: 24 February, 2015",all,Peethasaur,"Love this game. Each game is similar in duration to something like Settlers of Catan (except real time). As other have said, it's not a Civ type game where you spend weeks developing a civilization across the world. These matches were made to take about 45 min, and meant to be played comptetively online. That said, the AI is very good if you don't want to play others.Essentially, it plays out something like a Catan match would. You mine resources and then fight for the exclusive production of them. You also buy/sell from/to the 'bank'. Prices of resources are determined automatically by how much people are buying and selling. This means you can take strategies that short a resource you have a surplus of, and when the prices goes up you can sell your stash for a profit (the other players would hike the price up, because they must buy from the bank if they can't produce).You win by purchasing all of the stock of other players. Stock price is calculated by your total value (debt, cash on hand, production rate, HQ level, stock assets, etc.).The gameplay is great. God, I hope the voices get a makeover..."
