76561198383590060,Recommended,271240,31386210,Posted: 26 April,all,IanArcad,"As a sci fi economic RTS, Offworld Trading Company is a niche game, but for the right kind of player there's really nothing like it and I can't recommend it enough.  Single player, assuming you take advantages of saves and pauses, it plays like a tough simulation or even turn based game where you try to build a profitable company in a hostile environment before your AI opponents do.  But multiplayer is a whole different animal, it is fast and frantic, with split second strategic and economic decision making.  I played single player for months (on another platform), and stiil wasn't really ready for multiplayer, but I am having the time of my life trying to keep pace.  The music is also incredible.For those who familiar with the game but not the DLCs, the one to check out is Ceres, which is OTC but with some rule changes, new buildings, patents, etc.  The newest one, Io aka Jupiter's Forge is the same type of thing.  It's a lot of fun to see what works in these new environments and what doesn't."
