76561197961031285,Recommended,271240,14980572,"Posted: 20 March, 2015",all,Velocibacon,This review is written during Beta.OTC is an expansion/economics game which combines a procedurally generated map (replete with varying forms and quantity of resources) and a 'market' feature in which you trade the resources with other in-game players. The enjoyment of this game comes from using your awareness of the overall availability of resources on the map to predict which will become more valuable as the game progresses. Do well and your personal stock price raises; buy out 100% of the stock in competing players to win the game in the default play mode.Matches take anywhere from 10 to 25 minutes in my experience and are usually enjoyable all the way through.
