,Not Recommended,271240,34516112,Posted: 26 August,all,CB,"This is a tough one for me to write. I really LIKE Off World Trading Company. It's pretty. The mechanics are neat. The concept is innovative.The interface is great. The gameplay is fun. EXCEPT. Losing is REALLY frustrating. Maybe RTS players are used to this kind of thing (I don't like RTS games, personally), but when I lose I expect to learn something. I want to know what happened. I want to understand, analyse and get better. I want to not be completely surprised by failure. OTC fails all these checks. Despite neat mechanics, losses are sudden, often unexpected, and rarely teach anything. You can be feeling like you are doing well, and suddenly get overwhelmed by an opponent that you didn't know what a threat, and you don't even know why. And often I was left with the feeling that if I had just had a few seconds of warning, I could have stopped it from happening, but it happens so fast...I'm NOT an easily frustrated person. I'm used to not being very good at games, and very frequently losing at them. I learn from my mistakes and I try again. But, this game is really frustrating for me, and despite all the rest of the good in it, the surprise, seemingly random losses get me mad, and gets up my blood pressure when I'm trying to just relax and play a cool economy-fighting game.So, you may hear all this and be like ""Sweet, I love that,"" but for my part, I cannot recommend this game."
