76561198007513026,Not Recommended,271240,30068308,Posted: 20 February,all,malcolmmackay224,"After playing this game for a few hours I think a better name for OTC would be ""Mars - the spreadsheet"".Lots of numbers, lots of tweaking numbers. I love playing strategy games but I don't OTC to be much fun. The references to the classic Dan/Dani Bunten game MULE had me fooled. I was hoping for an elegantly designed game with deep strategy, a modern take on MULE. There is nothing elegant about the design of OTC.If your idea of fun is trying to figure out whether paying a couple of thousand dollars to increase the price of a resource by five dollars for 20 seconds is the optimal strategy, OTC may be the game for you. So many choices to make but none of them are particularly interesting.If you want to get a feel for the level of mind numbing detail in OTC, read the free Almanac before buying the game. This poorly written document is chock full of formulas - this game must have been designed by a programmer. I'm a programmer myself, but I don't want to tinker with formulas for fun.I've heard of other Stardock games being referred to as spreadsheet games. I thought OTC might be different but it seems that Stardock lacks the creative energy that is essential for creating compelling games."
