76561198061773358,Not Recommended,271240,14512866,"Posted: 17 February, 2015",all,Filane,"If you think Railroad Tycoon would be a better game with these game features, then Offworld Trading Company (OTC) would be for you:1. You can bomb your competitors' train stations, railroads and related structures;2. You can hire bandits to rob the opponents' train cargoes;3. You can use EMP to shut down the competitors' train systems; and4, You can sabotage the power supply of your opponents.I'm a fan of business / economic simulators and I don't think the above military / criminal / terrorist means of competing should be the gaming mechanics in a business sim. When I play a business sim, I want to use business / economic strategies to outsmart my competitors. I have no interest at all in using any military or criminal ways to win. Honestly, no matter how much AMD dislikes Intel and Nvidia, AMD wouldn't hire criminals to bomb or sabotage the opponents' fabrication plants, right?When I played Railroad Tycoon, I had the feeling of being the CEO of a growing railroad company. However, when I played Offworld Trading Company, I just felt like being the boss of a mafia business using criminal and military means to hurt my competitors. I don't like this feeling at all.The game description says there's ""no military"" in OTC but I think this's completely wrong and misleading. The in-game black market offers all the ""dirty tricks"" mentioned above to sabotage your competitors' businesses. I'm not sure whether this black market will change later, but, for now, I don't recommend this game to fans of business / economic sims."
