,Recommended,271240,18212857,"Posted: 26 September, 2015",all,Illeru,"A decent RTS game with some novel elements. 5/10 (6/10 considering early access).Very close to the CIV, tile like RTS, with limited tile ""claimability"" which means the strategic element of tile selection very important. Resource system works very well - it does play a lot like C&C in that regard and may lend itself too much to systematic builds (i.e. there is an optimum build order, stick to it or loose). There isn't a huge level of replayability there which is why I chose to write the review early - essentially the resources available adjust the location of HQ and thats it, every game plays out very similarly. A bit more depth in the building system and more to the takeover mechanism would make the game more worthy.Currently a good game to give a go if interested in RTS/builders. Consider waiting for it to be on special - not worth the current price.PROS:*Novel importance of the resource system, buying and selling is what this game is about.*Limit to the number of tiles makes claim selection very important* Resource system works very well, straight forward to use.* AI seems to work fairly wellCONS:* The Black Market system is opaque and seems redundant. The features become very expensive very quickly, and it is difficult to see how they really assist the player.*Resource tiles are largely irrelevant for most building types - find proximate resources then clump buildings together (doesn't quite come across as worthy)* Some of the controls are difficult to use (for example selecting a building to bring up context menu for deletion it - it keeps exiting the interface!)*Takeover system needs more depth and more response posibilities once the count down starts."
76561198109998189,Recommended,271240,18168761,"Posted: 23 September, 2015",all,riniort,"Awesome game for economist, you knew it worth the price.It's the mixture of being investor and real time game for tricky strategy excercise."
76561198024616922,Recommended,271240,16634352,"Posted: 22 June, 2015",all,Kraftword,"Offworld Trading Company brings a different type of strategy in a very interesting seting. The game feels very accessible, even to a player that is not used to fast paced strategy such as Starcraft 2.The games are also always interesting, as there are no real ""builds"" beacuse you need to adapt to the current situation. Sure, there are ""starters"", a early, mid and lategame, but the game does not have the sort of hard builds and hard counters to such builds, as often is the case in other RTS-type games.With addictive gameplay in singleplayer as well as multiplayer and with a innovative experience, though some mechanics such as the debt system needs some improvment, I highly recommend the game."
