76561197996780028,Recommended,271240,22109691,"Posted: 28 March, 2016",all,ReaperGT3,"Quick review...the game so far.I got this game during its first few weeks of appearing on the steam store. After installing I got to the main screen then it would crash back to steam. Ok I thought, its in beta so maybe its something they are working on to fix. I tried a few times over the weeks and still the same issue....that is until their latest update.I can now play the game <cheers all round>I play quite a few stratagy type games so jumped straight into a single player game. It did not go well and was bought out by rival corps pretty quickly as my stock price was low and I amounted a large amount of debt! So I hit up the tutorials which cover very basic gameplay and could do with hints on the way to improve stocks prices or reduce debt/cancel out debt all together.Yes there are diferent classes which have there own benifits/restrictions. For instance Expansive (human) require large amounts of food/water followed by power and oxygen. Robotic eats through Silicon and Power whereas Scavenger eats Carbon like theres no tomorrow!So what have I learnt in the past 10hrs of play..?!Ping quick at the start so you can find the best resourse spot on the map.You can plant your HQ down ontop of a resourse which adds it to your starting inventory but will not regenerate the resourse like it would if you just planted a mine ontop of the resourse.Try and keep modules attached to the HQ that way your not charged to transport across the map (Power also = fuel)Solar panels are good but shutdown at night and thats where debt can mount up quick if your transporting alot! Wind turbines work day and night which give a steady trickle of power. Geo thermal plants work best as they operate day and night and dont require transports but are expense!|The game has a steep learning curve currently which is brought about mainly due to the tutorials included with the game. I found out more through looking in the forums and youtube. Doing so I won my first game last night."
