76561198047443969,Recommended,271240,23848927,"Posted: 26 June, 2016",all,Hououin Kyouma,"An interesting economic simulation. It really puts you in the shoes of a business CEO. You have to choose which resources to buy and which to produce, as making everything slows you down to the point you can be overtaken rather quickly. The basic idea is that of a resource management game, one where the costs of every item are in flux, just like in the real commodities market, and you have to decide the best course of action. there are power-ups to help you control this, and four factions each with their own abilities. You can pause the game in single player, and while i haven't tried multiplayer yet, i believe it would be an interesting change of pace to play against humans. While this is an interesting game, bear in mind that you will do better if you have a basic understanding of supply and demand, at least at the start. (ie. flooding the market with one good will kill the price of it, destroying your revenue.)"
