,Recommended,271240,26043085,"Posted: 14 October, 2016",all,PerfectPencil,"Offword Trading company is a base building game...that's pretty much it. But that's amazingly NOT it. There is something really EXCITING about this game, and that taps into a real world scenario were a company attempts to become a monopoly and take out competition through the white and black markets. Buying out a competitor and turning them into a subsidy feels really good. Oddly good, actually. There is this odd feeling of power involved that i've never felt before from a game.To kind of put this into perspective I finished a match and had to sit back and stop for a while. My heart was racing and my palms were a little twitchy. I don't know how a game about building a base and mining resources got me to that state but.. somehow it did.Actually.. i know how. You know monopoly? This game reminds me of a particularily brutal Monopoly win. You know the kind.. where you own most of the board but start to auction off your chores to the highest bidder. When you don't just win, but emotionally crush your friends/family who are playing with you. Yea.. somehow this game taps into that exceptionally powerful and dark corner of our minds. Obliterating someone financially feels so much more powerful than just hsooting them with a gun like every other game. It's intense."
