76561198098422676,Recommended,271240,26132253,"Posted: 20 October, 2016",all,RedGreen,"I have enjoyed playing this game. There are a lot of complicated economic factors that require constant adjustment plus the use of subterfuge to increase your advantage.  If you like the economics of RTS, but not the war, this is the game for you."
76561198024727002,Recommended,271240,22715295,"Posted: 29 April, 2016",all,byronehoward1,"This game is a reminder of how great Early Access can be, despite all the disappointments we suffer out there when someone comes up with a great concept with all these ideas of what to do with it and is then faced with reality of either the cost of making it, how much time it will take, or simply losing interest in it and releasing a half-baked product or worse, a steaming pile instead of the promised game.That is not the case here.They had an amazing idea with this game.  RTS, but it isn't a military RTS.Wait...that exists?  I thought that was a prerequisite?  Not so!  This game is an RTS based on the competitiveness of business entrepreneurship in a fast paced minimal rule or even better 'make up the rules as you go environment' set on mars.  There are some very familiar RTS elements included in here, such as the upgrade system in between missions served by employees who make your buildings more efficient, resources to hunt for and grab quickly, logical progression of the build up of your 'base', and the black market, which functions a lot like a deployable powers in most RTS game, with potentially game altering mechanics.Pros:-New and innovative idea for the somewhat struggling and stagnant RTS genre.-Easy to learn, but complex and varying enough to make each drop a different decision and a different experience.-Great Dev time that listens to the players.-Great soundtrack.-Very good graphics for a smaller studio.-Polished gameplay.-Makes you really think both long term strategy with shorter term objectives that can change in an instant based on the market or other player actions.-The Campaign is more than just a tutorial, still a little short, but a very fun experience that makes you balance long term investing in certain resources versus the short-term map strategy of how you win, which can be won or lost based on how your long term strategy accounted for potential hiccups in your usual win strategy.Cons-The amount of time that will pass while you are playing this game without you noticing.-You may start saying in your head: ""Offworld Shipment Launched: Look at All The Money"" every time you see a plane or rocket take off.-You may start seeing people are work or school and wondering how you can commit espionage against them and not get caught.This game is very fun and a refreshing reminder of how great Early Access can be when done right.  Thank you for the great game you have created Mohawk games and being receptive to our feedback and suggestions!"
