76561197965744300,Recommended,271240,22945524,"Posted: 12 May, 2016",all,OBG{A}whiterp,"This is perhaps the most complex RTS game I have ever played. Like some other reviewers, the game it most reminds me of is StarCraft, only with dirty tricks instead of armed forces. In single player the AI is scheming and devious and while it plays by the same rules it is tough to beat and very rewarding when you do so. In multiplayer there are so many variables in play that it is very difficult, if not impossible to keep track of them all. One of the best parts of this game are the ""Learn to play"" scenarios. Many complicated games do a very poor job of introducing new players but the progressive scenarios here are great. Be sure to play them all before attempting a real game. I expect this game will provide me many hours of intriguing game play and what more can you ask of a game than that."
,Recommended,271240,22955530,"Posted: 13 May, 2016",all,Shinigami,"I've been playing since Early Access, and, despite a few issues the game had in the past, I liked it.Now, after the final release, I can say I like the game more than ever before!Its a fun little market simulator (buy low sell high kind of simulator), with some ""battle"" elements (you ""fight"" using dirty black market tricks, like hiring pirates, bribing people into giving you more land, making your stock price go up ect). The game is small but highly replayable.There is a single player mode, consisting of:- campaign (special mode, consisting of several games)- single-map skirmish vs AI (you can configure it as you please, including AI difficulty, number of players, size of the map ect)- daily challenge (play vs AI under fixed conditions, there is a leader board, faster win - higher place)And there's multiplayer mode which I never tried, but I believe its lots of fun. And very punishing to newbies, I believe, since this game is quite technical - you need to make right decisions fast.Overall, I'd give this game 4/5 stars. Its nice little fun game to play, innovative in some ways. I like it.I'm a big fan of economy sims in general, and there hasn't been many interesting games of this genre lately. Offworld Trading Company fits my tastes well, if a little sore on the difficulty side (AI gets on my nerves fast when it suddenly wins 3 games in a row). I still like it the way it is, though - if you play your cards right, you win."
