76561198258322781,Recommended,271240,30068776,Posted: 20 February,all,Nobody Expects Maximus!,"I'd been eyeing this game for a while, and a sale hit so I finally bought it. Wow, did the AI ever school me the first few times! Lots of options to play with: what resources do I harvest? Buy power or make it? Do I pick an HQ with raw materials or finished goods as primary build components? There's a great big difference between each HQ type, and the balance is pretty good, too. Depending on the map you pull and even where on that map you decide to explore to start out, you'll pick a different HQ. And you'll need to! There's just no way can one HQ type can win in every scenario, and I think that's another great indicator of the balance between each different HQ's strengths and weaknesses, and that really adds to the fun of learning and playing the game. I like random maps and skirmish so far, haven't got much beyond that, but I surely will. And boy does the black market and all the shenanigans available in THERE ever add some interesting gameplay dimensions! (But don't let your bond ratings fall too low, or you don't get to give, you'll just receive shenanigans. Yikes!) This game has a lot to enjoy, and I'm finishing a game in about 15-20 minutes, so it's not an all night commitment, either. Play 1 or 2, or 7 in a row, it's still fun. Highly recommended."
